ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width)) + 
    geom_point()

Customization with geom_point() options

ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width)) + 
  geom_point(color="orange", fill="#69b3a2", shape=21, alpha=0.5, size=6, stroke=2)

Using theme_ipsum

library(hrbrthemes)
ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width)) + 
  geom_point(color="black", fill="#69b3a2", shape=22, alpha=0.5, size=6, stroke=1) +
  theme_ipsum()

Map a variable to marker feature

# Transparency
ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width, alpha=Species)) + 
  geom_point(size=6, color="#69b3a2") +
  ggtitle("Transparency") +
  theme_ipsum()

# Shape
ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width, shape=Species)) + 
  geom_point(size=6, color="lightblue") +
  ggtitle("Shape") +
  theme_ipsum()

# Size
ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width, size=Petal.Width)) + 
  geom_point(color="darkred") +
  ggtitle("Size") +
  theme_ipsum()

Mapping to several features

# shape, transparency, size and color all depends on the Species value. 
ggplot(iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, y=Sepal.Width, shape=Species, alpha=Species, 
                 size=Species, color=Species)) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_ipsum()

Add text with geom_text()

data <- head(mtcars, 30)
 
ggplot(data, aes(x=wt, y=mpg)) +
  geom_point() + # Show dots
  geom_text(label=rownames(data), nudge_x = 0.25, nudge_y = 0.25, check_overlap = T)

Add labels with geom_label()

data <- head(mtcars, 30)
 
ggplot(data, aes(x=wt, y=mpg)) +
  geom_point() + # Show dots
  geom_label(label=rownames(data), nudge_x = 0.25, nudge_y = 0.25, check_overlap = T)

Add one text label only

data <- head(mtcars, 30)
 
ggplot(data, aes(x=wt, y=mpg)) +
  geom_point() + # Show dots
  geom_label(
    label="Look at this!", 
    x=4.1,
    y=20,
    # Rectangle size around label
    label.padding = unit(0.55, "lines"), 
    label.size = 0.35,
    color = "black",
    fill="#69b3a2"
  )

Add a group of text labels

library(dplyr)
library(tibble)
data <- head(mtcars, 30)

# Change data rownames as a real column
data <- data %>%
  rownames_to_column(var="carName")
  
ggplot(data, aes(x=wt, y=mpg)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_label(
    # Filter data first
    data=data %>% filter(mpg>20 & wt>3), 
    aes(label=carName)
  )

Add rug with geom_rug()

ggplot(data=iris, aes(x=Sepal.Length, Petal.Length)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_rug(col="steelblue",alpha=0.1, size=1.5)

Add a linear trend

library(ggplot2)
library(hrbrthemes)

# Create dummy data
data <- data.frame(
  cond = rep(c("condition_1", "condition_2"), each=10), 
  my_x = 1:100 + rnorm(100,sd=9), 
  my_y = 1:100 + rnorm(100,sd=16) 
)

head(data)
##          cond      my_x      my_y
## 1 condition_1 -3.940823  1.831761
## 2 condition_1 11.000620 13.461969
## 3 condition_1  5.344974  1.397194
## 4 condition_1 17.943684  8.075504
## 5 condition_1  9.647365 21.327342
## 6 condition_1  5.564345  3.984744

# with linear trend
ggplot(data, aes(x=my_x, y=my_y)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm , color="red", se=FALSE) +
  theme_ipsum()

# linear trend + confidence interval
ggplot(data, aes(x=my_x, y=my_y)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm , color="red", fill="#69b3a2", se=TRUE) +
  theme_ipsum()

Add multiple groups trend lines with labels

library(geomtextpath)

ggplot(iris, aes(x = Sepal.Length, 
                 y = Petal.Length, 
                 color = Species)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_labelsmooth(
    aes(label = Species), 
    fill = "white",
    method = "lm", 
    formula = y ~ x,
    size = 3, 
    linewidth = 1, 
    boxlinewidth = 0.4) +
  theme_bw() + 
  guides(color = 'none') # remove legend
